In the “Gartenflora,” 1866, page 335, Dr. Regel had characterised a new genus under the name of Gramma- tosorws, which is accompanied by a figure. It, however, appears to me to be founded on what may be termed an amorphous form of the sori of Aspidium alatum of Wallich, a large-growing Indian species, bearing numerous irregular sniall sori, which in specimens from Malacca are irregulan and confluent, forming linear transverse sori analogous to Memmium, while others on the same segment form linear sori parallel with the primary veins.
